00:00:00.730 --> 00:00:02.570
We were given two dice to roll.

00:00:02.570 --> 00:00:04.930
One is black with six sides.

00:00:04.930 --> 00:00:07.050
The other is white
with four sides.

00:00:07.050 --> 00:00:10.490
So a four-sided die is kind
of a pyramid-looking thing.

00:00:10.490 --> 00:00:13.420
It has exactly four sides.

00:00:13.420 --> 00:00:15.370
It would be a pyramid
with a triangular base.

00:00:15.370 --> 00:00:17.078
For a given roll, what
is the probability

00:00:17.078 --> 00:00:19.900
that the dice add up to 10?

00:00:19.900 --> 00:00:23.340
If it helps, you may select
the matching outcomes below.

00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:25.610
Your selections aren't
checked with your answer.

00:00:25.610 --> 00:00:27.230
So this might look a little
bit strange at first.

00:00:27.230 --> 00:00:28.688
You're like, what
is this triangle?

00:00:28.688 --> 00:00:32.940
This triangle is the face
of the four-sided die

00:00:32.940 --> 00:00:34.570
that is facing you.

00:00:34.570 --> 00:00:37.740
So this is the roll
of the four-sided die.

00:00:37.740 --> 00:00:39.380
So this is a roll of 1 and 1.

00:00:39.380 --> 00:00:41.089
So these clearly are
not adding up to 10.

00:00:41.089 --> 00:00:43.254
So let's think about all
the ones that add up to 10.

00:00:43.254 --> 00:00:44.316
So this adds up to 2.

00:00:44.316 --> 00:00:46.510
This adds up to 3.

00:00:46.510 --> 00:00:48.580
This adds up to 4.

00:00:48.580 --> 00:00:50.137
This adds up to 5.

00:00:50.137 --> 00:00:51.720
Let's see what
actually adds up to 10.

00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:55.560
So if we go all the way-- so
clearly, if we get a 4 and a 6,

00:00:55.560 --> 00:00:58.450
that's going to add up to 10.

00:00:58.450 --> 00:01:00.010
And are there any
other possibilities

00:01:00.010 --> 00:01:01.860
that add up to 10?

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:05.440
Well, the highest possible roll
I can get on a four-sided die

00:01:05.440 --> 00:01:06.790
is a 4.

00:01:06.790 --> 00:01:09.010
So that's my best scenario.

00:01:09.010 --> 00:01:10.660
That's the highest
possible roll.

00:01:10.660 --> 00:01:13.270
And even if I get that, I still
need the highest possible roll

00:01:13.270 --> 00:01:14.650
on the six-sided die.

00:01:14.650 --> 00:01:16.650
So this is the only
scenario that adds up to 10.

00:01:16.650 --> 00:01:18.316
You can look at any
of these other ones.

00:01:18.316 --> 00:01:20.250
They'll add up to
something less than 10.

00:01:20.250 --> 00:01:24.130
So there's one possibility
that satisfies our constraints.

00:01:24.130 --> 00:01:25.960
The dice add up to 10.

00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:28.750
And how many total equally
likely possibilities

00:01:28.750 --> 00:01:29.530
were there?

00:01:29.530 --> 00:01:30.030
Let's see.

00:01:30.030 --> 00:01:32.930
This grid shows all the
equally likely possibilities.

00:01:32.930 --> 00:01:37.120
This is 1, 2, 3, 4
times 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6.

00:01:37.120 --> 00:01:39.970
There are 24 equally
likely possibilities,

00:01:39.970 --> 00:01:43.320
and that comes from you
have 6 possibilities

00:01:43.320 --> 00:01:45.376
from the six-sided die
times 4 possibilities

00:01:45.376 --> 00:01:46.750
from the four-sided
die gives you

00:01:46.750 --> 00:01:49.440
24 equally likely possibilities.

00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:54.440
Only one satisfies
the constraint

00:01:54.440 --> 00:01:56.520
that the dice add up to 10.

00:01:56.520 --> 00:01:59.390
Let's do a few more of these.

00:01:59.390 --> 00:02:02.280
So you're given two
six-sided dice to roll.

00:02:02.280 --> 00:02:03.990
For a given roll, what
